base.contents:
The Bind method belongs to the wx.EvtHandler type. As binding calls usually go
self.Bind(event, handler, [source])
all the widgets are instances of wx.EvtHandler (and other classes through multiple inheritance).
The first arg ("event") to Bind(...) is an instance of wx.PyEventBinder. These look like wx.EVT_*.
The "handler" arg is a callable which takes exactly 1 argument, viz. the an object describing the detilas of the event.
If "source" is not specified, the source of the events will be assumed to be the widget having "handler" as its field. If this is not the case, use "source" to indicate explicitly the source of the events.
